defs.name: Analysis
defs.docs:
This is the main database that contains all the collected symbol information,
 such as definitions, their mapping between spans, hierarchy and so on,
 organized in a per-crate fashion.

defs.name: per_crate
defs.docs: Contains lowered data with global inter-crate `Id`s per each crate.

Reads raw analysis data for non-blacklisted crates from files in directories

defs.name: read_crate_data
defs.docs:
Attempts to read and deserialize `Analysis` data from a JSON file at `path`,
 returns `Some(data)` on success.

defs.name: loader
defs.docs:
Defines an `AnalysisLoader` trait, which allows to specify directories
 from which save-analysis JSON files can be read. Also supplies a 
 default implementation `CargoAnalysisLoader` for Cargo-emitted save-analysis
 files.

defs.name: AnalysisLoader
defs.docs:
Allows to specify from where and which analysis files will be considered
 when reloading data to lower.

defs.name: CrateReader
defs.docs:
Responsible for processing the raw `data::Analysis`, including translating
 from local crate ids to global crate ids, and creating lowered
 `PerCrateAnalysis`.

defs.name: crate_map
defs.docs:
This is effectively a map from local crate id -> global crate id, where
 local crate id are indices 0...external_crate_count.

defs.name: Id
defs.docs:
A common identifier for definitions, references etc. This is effectively a
 `DefId` with globally unique crate number (instead of a compiler generated
 crate-local number).
